# 🚀 COMPLETE GIT & GITHUB WORKFLOW (MULTI-BRANCH)

## 🏢 REAL-WORLD SCENARIO

In a real company project, multiple branches are used:

* **main** → Production (stable code)
* **dev** → Integration/testing branch
* **feature-* ** → Individual developer work

Example:

* feature-login
* feature-camera
* feature-payment (your branch)

---

## 🎯 OBJECTIVE

You will:

* Work on your own branch
* Push your code to GitHub
* Merge your work into dev/main

---

# 🔽 STEP 1: CLONE PROJECT (FIRST TIME)

```bash
git clone https://github.com/project.git
cd project
```

---

# 🔄 STEP 2: FETCH ALL BRANCHES

```bash
git fetch --all
```

✔ Downloads all branches from remote

---

# 📂 STEP 3: CHECK AVAILABLE BRANCHES

```bash
git branch -a
```

Example output:

```
main
dev
origin/feature-login
origin/feature-camera
```

---

# 🎯 STEP 4: SWITCH TO BASE BRANCH (DEV)

```bash
git checkout dev
git pull origin dev
```

✔ Ensures you have latest team code

---

# 🌿 STEP 5: CREATE YOUR FEATURE BRANCH

```bash
git checkout -b feature-payment
```

✔ Work safely without affecting others

---

# 💻 STEP 6: DO YOUR WORK

Examples:

* Add API
* Update UI
* Fix bugs

---

# 💾 STEP 7: COMMIT YOUR CHANGES

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "payment feature added"
```

✔ Saves your work locally

---

# 🔄 STEP 8: SYNC WITH LATEST DEV (VERY IMPORTANT)

```bash
git checkout dev
git pull origin dev

git checkout feature-payment
git merge dev
```

✔ Keeps your branch updated
✔ Avoids merge conflicts later

---

# 🚀 STEP 9: PUSH YOUR BRANCH

```bash
git push origin feature-payment
```

✔ Uploads your code to GitHub

---

# 🔀 STEP 10: CREATE PULL REQUEST (PR)

In GitHub:

* Base branch → dev
* Compare branch → feature-payment

✔ Team reviews your code
✔ Merge into dev

---

# 🔁 STEP 11: AFTER MERGE

```bash
git checkout dev
git pull origin dev
```

✔ Updates your local dev branch

---

# 🧹 STEP 12: DELETE FEATURE BRANCH (OPTIONAL)

```bash
git branch -d feature-payment
```

---

# 🔥 COMPLETE FLOW (SHORT VERSION)

```bash
git clone <repo>
cd repo

git checkout dev
git pull origin dev

git checkout -b feature-payment

# work
git add .
git commit -m "feature added"

git checkout dev
git pull origin dev

git checkout feature-payment
git merge dev

git push origin feature-payment
```

---

# ⚠️ TEAM WORKFLOW EXAMPLE

Two developers:

* You → feature-payment
* Other dev → feature-camera

Flow:

feature branches → dev → main

---

# 🧠 BRANCH PURPOSE

| Branch    | Purpose             |
| --------- | ------------------- |
| main      | Production          |
| dev       | Integration/testing |
| feature-* | Developer work      |

---

# 🚨 COMMON MISTAKES

❌ Working directly on main
❌ Not pulling before merge
❌ Not syncing with dev

---

# 💡 PRO TIP

Always follow:

```
dev → feature → dev → main
```

---

# 🔥 FINAL MINDSET

* You are NEVER working alone
* Always sync with team
* Always use branches

